===Reservoirs===

The Dnieper's last 800 kilometres before it flows into the Black Sea is an almost consecutive chain of reservoirs, all of them being located in Ukraine. They were built along with the river's hydroelectric stations during the [[Soviet Union]], and are used to generate hydroelectric power, providing around ten percent of Ukraine's electricity. The reservoirs include: [[Kiev Reservoir|Kiev]] (922 km<U+00B2>), [[Kaniv Reservoir|Kaniv]] (675 km<U+00B2>), [[Kremenchuk Reservoir|Kremenchuk]] (2,250 km<U+00B2>), [[Dniprodzerzhynsk Reservoir|Dniprodzerzhynsk]] (567 km<U+00B2>), [[Dnieper Reservoir|Dnieper ]] (420 km<U+00B2>), and [[Kakhovka Reservoir|Kakhovka]] (2,155 km<U+00B2>).  The dams forming these are used to generate hydroelectric power, 

